# Docker Compose First

- Use `docker compose` as the primary way to run the stack.
- Prefer containerized commands for backend, frontend, and test execution.
- For tests, prefer `docker compose --profile test run --rm --build backend-tests` and `docker compose --profile test run --rm --build frontend-tests`.
- Keep the documented workflow aligned with the Compose services and ports.
- When adding new commands, document the `docker compose` equivalent first.
